results.name: Number of inequivalent leaf-colorings of series-reduced rooted trees with n nodes.
comment: In a series-reduced rooted tree, every non-leaf node has at least two branches.
example: Inequivalent representatives of the a(6) = 23 leaf-colorings:
program: (PARI) \\ See links in A339645 for combinatorial species functions.
cycleIndexSeries(n)={my(v=vector(n)); v[1]=sv(1); for(n=2, #v, v[n] = polcoef( sEulerT(x*Ser(concat(v[1..n-2], [0]))), n-1 )); x*Ser(v)}
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Aug 21 2018
ext: Terms a(8) and beyond from _Andrew Howroyd_, Dec 11 2020
